        "text": "1 Kings 10:14-22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and the commentary there on this section, which is identical in both narratives, with the exception of some trifling differences. Before מביאים והסּחרים the relative pronoun is to be supplied: \"and what the merchants brought.\" As to the derivation of the word פּחות, which comes from the Aramaic form פּחה, governor (",
        "children": []
      },
